  </div><div class="page-break" style="margin-top:18pt"></div><div class="section-mast"><div class="num">01</div><div class="label"><span class="eyebrow">Section 01</span><h2>Executive Summary</h2></div></div><div class="score-big"><div class="number">0.0</div><div class="out-of">out of 10.0</div><div class="rec" style="background:#7A1B1B;color:#FFFFFF;">PASS</div></div><p class="narrative">This institutional-grade market study evaluates <strong>Newstead, PA</strong> for new residential construction feasibility. The analysis synthesizes data from 18+ government and commercial data sources including the U.S. Census Bureau, FRED, BLS, BEA, HUD, FHFA, Zillow, Redfin, RapidAPI Realtor.com, Parcl Labs, and SEC EDGAR filings, with AI-assisted synthesis via Anthropic Claude.</p><h3>Key Findings</h3><div class="kpi-grid four"><div class="kpi"><div class="value">3,847</div><div class="label">Population</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="value accent">$68,420</div><div class="label">Median HH Income</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="value green">—</div><div class="label">Monthly Absorption</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="value blue">—</div><div class="label">Annual Demand Gap</div></div></div><div class="page-break" style="margin-top:18pt"></div><div class="section-mast"><div class="num">02</div><div class="label"><span class="eyebrow">Section 02</span><h2>Market Area</h2></div></div><p class="narrative">The market study covers <strong>Newstead</strong>, a township-level market within Erie County County, PA, part of the Erie, PA Metro Area metro area.</p><dl class="def-list"><dt>Target Area</dt><dd>Newstead</dd><dt>Subdivision/Township</dt><dd>Newstead township</dd><dt>County</dt><dd>Erie County</dd><dt>State</dt><dd>PA</dd><dt>CBSA (Metro)</dt><dd>Erie, PA Metro Area</dd><dt>State FIPS</dt><dd>42</dd><dt>County FIPS</dt><dd>049</dd><dt>Subdivision FIPS</dt><dd>54112</dd><dt>ZIP Codes</dt><dd>16428</dd><dt>Coordinates</dt><dd>42.0919, -80.1502</dd></dl><p class="narrative" style="font-size:8.5pt;color:#6B7280;"><em>Note on data scope:</em> Demographic and housing metrics are reported at the most granular geography available from each source. County-level series (permits, employment, price indices) are labeled as such; sub-county metrics are reported at the township/subdivision level when available.</p><div class="page-break" style="margin-top:18pt"></div><div class="section-mast"><div class="num">03</div><div class="label"><span class="eyebrow">Section 03</span><h2>Demographics</h2></div></div><p class="narrative">The demographic profile of Newstead, PA reveals a population base of 3,847 residents across 1,512 households. The median household income of $68,420 indicates a middle-income market.</p><div class="kpi-grid"><div class="kpi"><div class="value">3,847</div><div class="label">Population</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="value">—</div><div class="label">5-Year Growth</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="value accent">$68,420</div><div class="label">Median HH Income</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="value">1,512</div><div class="label">Households</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="value">—</div><div class="label">Homeownership Rate</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="value">0.048%</div><div class="label">Unemployment Rate</div></div></div><table><tr><th>Indicator</th><th class="text-right">Value</th></tr><tr><td>Median Age</td><td class="text-right">—</td></tr><tr><td>Avg Household Size</td><td class="text-right">—</td></tr><tr><td>Per Capita Income</td><td class="text-right">—</td></tr><tr><td>MHI Growth (YoY)</td><td class="text-right">—</td></tr><tr><td>Poverty Rate</td><td class="text-right">—</td></tr><tr><td>Vacancy Rate</td><td class="text-right">0.102%</td></tr><tr><td>Affordable Ceiling</td><td class="text-right">—</td></tr><tr><td>Commute Inflow</td><td class="text-right">—</td></tr><tr><td>Commute Outflow</td><td class="text-right">—</td></tr></table><div class="page-break" style="margin-top:18pt"></div><div class="section-mast"><div class="num">04</div><div class="label"><span class="eyebrow">Section 04</span><h2>Housing Supply &amp; Inventory</h2></div></div><div class="kpi-grid four"><div class="kpi"><div class="value">—</div><div class="label">Total Units</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="value accent">0.841</div><div class="label">Owner-Occ</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="value blue">0.159</div><div class="label">Renter-Occ</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="value red">0.102%</div><div class="label">Vacancy</div></div></div><h3>Value &amp; Rent</h3><table><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Value</th></tr><tr><td>Median Home Value</td><td>$198,000</td></tr><tr><td>Median Gross Rent</td><td>$1,250</td></tr></table></div><div class="page-break" style="margin-top:18pt"></div><div class="section-mast"><div class="num">05</div><div class="label"><span class="eyebrow">Section 05</span><h2>Building Permits &amp; Construction Activity</h2></div></div><p class="narrative">No permit data available for this market.</p></div><div class="page-break" style="margin-top:18pt"></div><div class="section-mast"><div class="num">06</div><div class="label"><span class="eyebrow">Section 06</span><h2>Competitive Landscape</h2></div></div><div class="kpi-grid four"><div class="kpi"><div class="value">—</div><div class="label">Active Listings</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="value accent">$—</div><div class="label">Median List</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="value blue">58</div><div class="label">Days on Market</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="value green">2</div><div class="label">Active Builders</div></div></div><h3>Active Builders (Top 2)</h3><table><tr><th>Builder</th><th>Communities</th><th>Price Range</th><th>Avg Sqft</th><th>$/Sqft</th></tr><tr><td>Local Custom Builders</td><td>2</td><td>$245,000–$385,000</td><td>—</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>Keystone Custom Homes</td><td>1</td><td>$295,000–$445,000</td><td>—</td><td>—</td></tr></table></div><div class="page-break" style="margin-top:18pt"></div><div class="section-mast"><div class="num">07</div><div class="label"><span class="eyebrow">Section 07</span><h2>Absorption Analysis</h2></div></div><div class="kpi-grid"><div class="kpi"><div class="value accent">—</div><div class="label">Sales / Mo</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="value">—</div><div class="label">Annual Sales</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="value blue">— mo</div><div class="label">Months Supply</div></div></div></div><div class="page-break" style="margin-top:18pt"></div><div class="section-mast"><div class="num">08</div><div class="label"><span class="eyebrow">Section 08</span><h2>Pricing Strategy</h2></div></div></div><div class="page-break" style="margin-top:18pt"></div><div class="section-mast"><div class="num">09</div><div class="label"><span class="eyebrow">Section 09</span><h2>Land Acquisition</h2></div></div><div class="kpi-grid four"><div class="kpi"><div class="value">$—</div><div class="label">$/Lot Target</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="value accent">—</div><div class="label">% of Revenue</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="value blue">$—</div><div class="label">Finished Lot</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="value green">—</div><div class="label">Lots/Acre</div></div></div></div><div class="page-break" style="margin-top:18pt"></div><div class="section-mast"><div class="num">10</div><div class="label"><span class="eyebrow">Section 10</span><h2>Pro Forma Financials</h2></div></div><div class="kpi-grid four"><div class="kpi"><div class="value accent">$11,130,000</div><div class="label">Revenue</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="value">$—</div><div class="label">Gross Profit</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="value green">0.18%</div><div class="label">GP Margin</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="value blue">—</div><div class="label">Net Margin</div></div></div><h3>Forbes Capretto Homes Margin Gate</h3><div class="narrative">Forbes Capretto underwrites to a <strong>25-31% gross margin</strong> band (lower end for entry-level, upper end for premium/luxury). This scenario: <strong style="color:#EF4444">MATERIALLY BELOW target</strong> at 0.18%.</div><h3>SEC EDGAR Public Builder Benchmarks (latest 10-K)</h3><p class="narrative" style="font-size:8.5pt;color:#6B7280;">Source: SEC EDGAR companyfacts. Revenue / GP / ASP / cancellation rate extracted from most recent 10-K per builder. <strong>0 of 2 builders</strong> had 10-K data resolvable at render time; remaining rows render dashes honestly.</p><table><tr><th>Builder</th><th class="text-right">Revenue</th><th class="text-right">GP Margin</th><th class="text-right">Homes Delivered</th><th class="text-right">ASP</th><th class="text-right">Cancel Rate</th><th class="text-right">Filing</th></tr><tr><td>Local Custom Builders</td><td class="text-right">—</td><td class="text-right">—</td><td class="text-right">—</td><td class="text-right">—</td><td class="text-right">—</td><td class="text-right" style="font-size:8.5pt;color:#6B7280;">—</td></tr><tr><td>Keystone Custom Homes</td><td class="text-right">—</td><td class="text-right">—</td><td class="text-right">—</td><td class="text-right">—</td><td class="text-right">—</td><td class="text-right" style="font-size:8.5pt;color:#6B7280;">—</td></tr></table></div><div class="page-break" style="margin-top:18pt"></div><div class="section-mast"><div class="num">11</div><div class="label"><span class="eyebrow">Section 11</span><h2>Regulatory Environment</h2></div></div><h3>Impact Fees / Exactions</h3><table><tr><th>Fee Type</th><th>Amount</th></tr></table></div><div class="page-break" style="margin-top:18pt"></div><div class="section-mast"><div class="num">12</div><div class="label"><span class="eyebrow">Section 12</span><h2>Market Scorecard</h2></div></div><div class="score-summary" style="background:#7A1B1B;border-radius:8px;padding:20px;margin:16px 0;text-align:center;"><div style="font-size:36pt;font-weight:700;color:#FFFFFF;">0.0 / 10</div><div style="font-size:14pt;color:#FFFFFF;font-weight:600;margin-top:6px;">PASS</div></div></div><div class="page-break" style="margin-top:18pt"></div><div class="section-mast"><div class="num">13</div><div class="label"><span class="eyebrow">Section 13</span><h2>SWOT Analysis</h2></div></div><div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:12px;margin:14px 0;"><div style="background:#ECFDF5;border-left:4px solid #10B981;padding:14px;border-radius:4px;"><h3 style="color:#10B981;margin-top:0;">Strengths</h3><ul style="margin:0;padding-left:18px;"><li style="font-size:9pt;margin-bottom:4px;">Low land cost ($32k/acre) preserves margin headroom</li><li style="font-size:9pt;margin-bottom:4px;">By-right zoning reduces entitlement risk</li></ul></div><div style="background:#FEF2F2;border-left:4px solid #EF4444;padding:14px;border-radius:4px;"><h3 style="color:#EF4444;margin-top:0;">Weaknesses</h3><ul style="margin:0;padding-left:18px;"><li style="font-size:9pt;margin-bottom:4px;">5.4 months supply = balanced-to-slow absorption</li><li style="font-size:9pt;margin-bottom:4px;">MHI below state median limits pricing ceiling</li></ul></div><div style="background:#EFF6FF;border-left:4px solid #3B82F6;padding:14px;border-radius:4px;"><h3 style="color:#3B82F6;margin-top:0;">Opportunities</h3><ul style="margin:0;padding-left:18px;"><li style="font-size:9pt;margin-bottom:4px;">Underserved Premium tier ($295-385k) with only 1 active builder</li></ul></div><div style="background:#FFFBEB;border-left:4px solid #F59E0B;padding:14px;border-radius:4px;"><h3 style="color:#F59E0B;margin-top:0;">Threats</h3><ul style="margin:0;padding-left:18px;"><li style="font-size:9pt;margin-bottom:4px;">Erie MSA population decline trend</li><li style="font-size:9pt;margin-bottom:4px;">Higher rate environment compresses Entry-tier affordability</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="page-break" style="margin-top:18pt"></div><div class="section-mast"><div class="num">14</div><div class="label"><span class="eyebrow">Section 14</span><h2>Data Sources &amp; Methodology</h2></div></div><p class="narrative">This market study was assembled from 18 authoritative data sources, combining government statistics, commercial listings, and AI-driven analysis.</p><table><tr><th>Source</th><th>Data Provided</th><th>Last Updated</th></tr><tr><td>U.S. Census Bureau ACS</td><td>5-Year American Community Survey — population, income, housing characteristics</td><td>Current</td></tr><tr><td>U.S. Census Bureau PEP</td><td>Population Estimates Program — annual population estimates</td><td>Current</td></tr><tr><td>U.S. Census Bureau LODES</td><td>LEHD Origin-Destination Employment Statistics — commute flows</td><td>Current</td></tr><tr><td>Census CBP</td><td>County Business Patterns — employment by NAICS sector</td><td>Current</td></tr><tr><td>FRED / BLS</td><td>Federal Reserve Economic Data — unemployment rate, LAUS series</td><td>Current</td></tr><tr><td>BEA</td><td>Bureau of Economic Analysis — per capita personal income</td><td>Current</td></tr><tr><td>Census BPS</td><td>Building Permits Survey — residential permits by unit type</td><td>Current</td></tr><tr><td>HUD FMR</td><td>Fair Market Rents — rental rates by bedroom count</td><td>Current</td></tr><tr><td>FHFA HPI</td><td>Federal Housing Finance Agency — House Price Index</td><td>Current</td></tr><tr><td>Zillow ZHVI</td><td>Zillow Home Value Index — monthly home value trend</td><td>Current</td></tr><tr><td>Redfin</td><td>Redfin data center — DOM, sale-to-list, months supply</td><td>Current</td></tr><tr><td>RapidAPI Realtor.com</td><td>New construction filter — active communities</td><td>Current</td></tr><tr><td>NewHomeSource</td><td>Community listings &amp; pricing</td><td>Current</td></tr><tr><td>Parcl Labs</td><td>Price-per-square-foot and inventory metrics</td><td>Current</td></tr><tr><td>SEC EDGAR</td><td>Public builder 10-K filings — gross margins, ASP, cancellation rates</td><td>Current</td></tr><tr><td>BLS PPI</td><td>Producer Price Index — construction cost inflation</td><td>Current</td></tr><tr><td>Anthropic Claude API</td><td>claude-sonnet-4-6 — structured market analysis, scoring, SWOT</td><td>Current</td></tr><tr><td>Infinity Markets</td><td>Report generated 2026-04-22</td><td>Current</td></tr></table><h3>Methodology</h3><p class="narrative">Demographic data is sourced from the U.S. Census Bureau (ACS 5-year estimates) and Bureau of Labor Statistics. Housing inventory is pulled from Redfin, Zillow ZHVI, and MLS feeds via RapidAPI Realtor. Competitive intelligence combines NewHomeSource active listings with SEC EDGAR filings for public builders. Absorption, pricing, land, and pro forma analysis is synthesized using Claude Sonnet 4 against the aggregated dataset. The market scorecard applies a weighted 10-factor methodology calibrated to Forbes Capretto Homes underwriting criteria.</p><div class="footer-note" style="margin-top:24px;padding-top:12px;border-top:1px solid #E5E7EB;font-size:8pt;color:#6B7280;">Infinity Markets — Institutional Market Intelligence Platform. Report generated 4/22/2026, 5:00:00 PM.</div></div><div class="page-break" style="margin-top:18pt"></div><div class="section-mast"><div class="num">A</div><div class="label"><span class="eyebrow">Appendix A</span><h2>Source Manifest · Provenance Trail</h2></div></div><p class="lede">Every value rendered in this report carries a provenance classifier. This appendix is the audit trail: per-field, the canonical name, the rendered value, the provenance class (measured / derived / modeled / LLM / missing), the upstream source URL, when it was fetched, and the confidence band.</p><p class="narrative" style="font-style:italic;color:#6B6B66;">No <code>_env</code> envelopes are persisted on this study yet. Provenance was inferred at render time from the canonical fields. Future regenerations will surface the full manifest here once the schema migration 004 columns are populated upstream.</p></body></html>